   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="translation">
            <ab>To Flavius Sarapammon and Flavius Serenos, the venerable proximi of this city, from Philoxenos, from the same city.  I made an exchange of property with Apollon, [l. 5] son of Akoutas, in the presence of seven competent witnesses, and after many days of the exchange (i.e. many days after the exchange was made) and while two carats were still owed to me . . .</ab>
